removed meaningless statement "do not measure temperature directly". neither do thermometers. Temperature is the average velocity of molecules. We don't measure temperature directly. We measure the effect of temp on something, e.g.  mercury.

The temperature is calculated from physical measurements using the laws of physics not "inferred". Even when measured by thermometers it is calculated by measuring the effect that the temperature has on mercury.
